1
00:00:16,666 --> 00:00:19,833
[ASAHINA sobs]

2
00:00:19,916 --> 00:00:21,708
Pull it together...

3
00:00:21,791 --> 00:00:23,750
Crying's not gonna help...

4
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:26,291
Sure, things are real bad...

5
00:00:26,375 --> 00:00:29,791
Fact: They're awful...

6
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:32,208
But you got this, 'kay?

7
00:00:32,291 --> 00:00:35,333
Maybe just treat yourself
to a li'l midnight snack.

8
00:00:35,416 --> 00:00:36,791
Like a donut.

9
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:46,625
Heh...

10
00:00:46,708 --> 00:00:49,083
[ASAHINA screams]

11
00:02:26,291 --> 00:02:28,541
[NAEGI] Murder number two.

12
00:02:28,625 --> 00:02:30,750
Gender-bending Fujisaki...

13
00:02:30,833 --> 00:02:33,000
Killed by Ohwada.

14
00:02:33,083 --> 00:02:34,458
Why?

15
00:02:34,541 --> 00:02:36,500
Why is whoever's
behind this whole thing

16
00:02:36,583 --> 00:02:39,625
so bent on turning
us into monsters?

17
00:02:39,708 --> 00:02:41,458
The day after
Ohwada's trial,

18
00:02:41,541 --> 00:02:44,333
we were granted access
to the third floor.

19
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:48,166
No signs of an out there.
Surprise, surprise...

20
00:02:48,250 --> 00:02:50,125
We're still trapped
liked animals.

21
00:02:50,208 --> 00:02:53,125
And help is definitely
not on the way.

22
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:56,166
[NAEGI] Wow...

23
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:59,333
[NAEGI] So, same as before.

24
00:02:59,416 --> 00:03:01,416
Our situation is desperate.

25
00:03:04,666 --> 00:03:06,500
[NAEGI] Poor Ishimaru.

26
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:10,833
He hasn't said a word.
Not since Ohwada's execution.

27
00:03:13,041 --> 00:03:14,291
[MONOKUMA laughs]

28
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:16,000
[MONOKUMA] Hop to, half-asses!

29
00:03:16,083 --> 00:03:17,708
Toddle your haggard
little selves

30
00:03:17,791 --> 00:03:20,166
over to the gymnasium,
on zee double!

31
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:22,250
And try not to
get lost on the way.

32
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,333
Explanation is forthcomin'.

33
00:03:27,291 --> 00:03:28,500
[NAEGI] Huh.

34
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:30,000
You guys are already here?

35
00:03:30,083 --> 00:03:31,291
That didn't take long.

36
00:03:31,375 --> 00:03:33,916
So... What came of
the homicidal maniac?

37
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,375
Ugh... Why's the peanut
gallery gawking at me?

38
00:03:36,458 --> 00:03:39,291
A simple sneeze reverts her
back to her "cheerful" self.

39
00:03:39,375 --> 00:03:41,958
Seriously? That's a bit clichéd.

40
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:43,875
Like you have any room to talk!

41
00:03:43,958 --> 00:03:47,041
[MONOKUMA] Hail, hail!
The gang's all here.

42
00:03:59,166 --> 00:04:01,791
What sadistic scheme
have you cooked up now?

43
00:04:01,875 --> 00:04:03,291
[MONOKUMA laughs]

44
00:04:03,375 --> 00:04:06,041
[MONOKUMA] That's the
Million Dollar Question!

45
00:04:08,375 --> 00:04:10,000
[MONOKUMA]
Well, ten million actually.

46
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:13,333
Yes, kiddies: this mountain
of moolah can be yours,

47
00:04:13,416 --> 00:04:18,416
if you graduate! Pretty
sweet, right? Eh? Eh?

48
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:20,791
That's a whole lotta cash...

49
00:04:21,958 --> 00:04:24,750
Is life so cheap you would
label it with a price tag?

50
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:27,333
I know what you're
tryin' to do!

51
00:04:27,416 --> 00:04:30,750
We're not gonna massacre
each other for money, period!

52
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:32,250
[MONOKUMA laughs]

53
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:35,083
[MONOKUMA] Sure. Whatever
you say, Saint Francis.

54
00:04:35,166 --> 00:04:37,875
I'll just leave you fine,
upstanding coeds

55
00:04:37,958 --> 00:04:40,916
to scratch out a living
as professional students.

56
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:44,916
Money-money-money-money...

57
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,708
Fine I'll be the one to say it:

58
00:04:46,791 --> 00:04:48,458
You know somebody
here's hurtin' for cash.

59
00:04:48,541 --> 00:04:49,708
[HAGAKURE whistles]

60
00:04:49,791 --> 00:04:51,291
Quiet your minds.

61
00:04:51,375 --> 00:04:54,666
If we give credence to money,
our situation will only worsen.

62
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:56,333
[FUKAWA] Oh, you think?!

63
00:04:56,416 --> 00:04:58,416
So the lure of
escape wasn't enough.

64
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:01,041
The mastermind will pull
whatever strings he can

65
00:05:01,125 --> 00:05:02,958
to pit us against each other.

66
00:05:03,041 --> 00:05:04,916
Adapting to life as
fellow prisoners

67
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,458
is our only
means of survival.

68
00:05:06,541 --> 00:05:07,333
[ASAHINA sighs]

69
00:05:07,416 --> 00:05:09,666
Asahina... What is the matter?

70
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:13,000
It's nothing. I mean it's just
that-- Don't think I'm crazy...

71
00:05:13,083 --> 00:05:13,958
But um...

72
00:05:14,041 --> 00:05:15,750
I think I might've...

73
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:18,000
seen the ghost of Fujisaki.

74
00:05:19,166 --> 00:05:22,041
[ASAHINA} Yesterday,
actually. In here.

75
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:23,958
Thanks for giving me
the heebie-jeebies.

76
00:05:24,041 --> 00:05:25,458
I do believe in spooks...

77
00:05:25,541 --> 00:05:27,625
--[FUKAWA] What are you doing?!
--Yamada! Not cool, brah!

78
00:05:27,708 --> 00:05:30,541
It'll get ticked and
come for us in our sleep!

79
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:32,000
Wait...

80
00:05:34,416 --> 00:05:36,166
Didn't this belong to...?

81
00:05:36,250 --> 00:05:37,625
Then how come...?

82
00:05:39,583 --> 00:05:41,625
Somebody just left it here?

83
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:43,125
Haven't you noticed?

84
00:05:43,208 --> 00:05:44,416
The layout of this room...

85
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:46,875
There's a very
important difference here.

86
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:52,375
There're no surveillance
cameras. At all.

87
00:05:52,458 --> 00:05:53,958
[ALL gasp]

88
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:55,166
Yes, that's right.

89
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:58,041
Monokuma can't see or hear us.

90
00:05:58,125 --> 00:06:02,083
Which makes this an
ideal hiding place.

91
00:06:02,166 --> 00:06:04,666
Hi, there! Good to
see you, master.

92
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:06,541
--A g-g-g-ghost!
--A g-g-g-ghost!

93
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:07,791
--I tap two black mana...
--I tap two black mana...

94
00:06:07,875 --> 00:06:11,083
Calm down...
It's a computer.

95
00:06:11,166 --> 00:06:12,166
Wait...

96
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:14,208
Master, where'd you go?

97
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:15,750
What is going on?

98
00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:20,333
Well, hello-hello! Welcome!

99
00:06:20,416 --> 00:06:21,750
I'm Alter Ego!

100
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:24,250
A specially designed artificial
intelligence program!

101
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:26,791
So creepy; the voice
sounds exactly like him.

102
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:29,291
That is slightly unnerving.

103
00:06:29,375 --> 00:06:32,041
It's not uncommon for
hackers to make vanity avatars.

104
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:33,625
Remember: Fujisaki
was something

105
00:06:33,708 --> 00:06:36,583
of a programming prodigy before
being ensnared by this place.

106
00:06:39,083 --> 00:06:41,125
Analyzing all files
on this hard drive.

107
00:06:41,208 --> 00:06:43,458
Gimme just a second, please.

108
00:06:43,541 --> 00:06:44,666
[ALTER EGO sighs]

109
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:46,000
The encryption's insane!

110
00:06:46,083 --> 00:06:48,333
I dunno, something tells me
files this protected

111
00:06:48,416 --> 00:06:49,791
must belong to Hope's Peak.

112
00:06:52,041 --> 00:06:54,625
Anything to give us
an advantage over Monokuma.

113
00:06:54,708 --> 00:06:56,750
It's about time
we had a little luck!

114
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,791
You may well have
found our escape.

115
00:06:58,875 --> 00:06:59,708
[ASAHINA giggles]

116
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:01,250
[ALTER EGO] Um...

117
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:04,750
So guys, I haven't seen Master
for while. Know where he is?

118
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,208
[ALTER EGO gasps]

119
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:18,208
I understand...

120
00:07:18,291 --> 00:07:20,250
I was prepared...

121
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:21,500
Poor li'l thing...

122
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:24,916
It's like some kinda
digital ronin now.

123
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,791
[ALTER EGO] It was only
a matter of time...

124
00:07:28,208 --> 00:07:29,916
You're still with us...

125
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,958
Y'never really died.

126
00:07:32,041 --> 00:07:33,666
Ishimaru, hi.

127
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,500
[ISHIMARU sobs]

128
00:07:35,583 --> 00:07:36,333
[ISHIMARU] It's okay...

129
00:07:36,416 --> 00:07:38,208
if you hate me...

130
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:40,708
I-I understand...

131
00:07:40,791 --> 00:07:45,166
I couldn't stop him
from doing what he did.

132
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:47,458
I was a coward!

133
00:07:55,791 --> 00:07:56,916
Uh-oh...

134
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,416
You feel responsible
for what happened to me.

135
00:08:01,208 --> 00:08:02,625
Lighten up.

136
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:04,708
Dude, you can't carry the
weight of the world on your back

137
00:08:04,791 --> 00:08:05,791
for something I did.

138
00:08:05,875 --> 00:08:07,083
[ISHIMARU gasps]

139
00:08:07,166 --> 00:08:08,666
Ohwada?!

140
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:10,333
Wow... this is, uh...

141
00:08:10,416 --> 00:08:12,708
I made my own decisions.

142
00:08:12,791 --> 00:08:15,875
Mullin' over a buncha what-ifs
aint' gonna do you any good.

143
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:17,333
This wasn't your fault.

144
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:21,166
[OHWADA] I'm my own
man. Just like you.

145
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:22,083
Thing is...

146
00:08:22,166 --> 00:08:24,083
You wanna feel angry, fine.

147
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:26,041
Just don't marinate in it;

148
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:28,166
use it for something
that's worth it.

149
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:31,125
Might manage to wake yourself up
from this nightmare.

150
00:08:31,208 --> 00:08:33,041
Gotta be ready, don'tcha?

151
00:08:33,125 --> 00:08:36,041
Think about it, bro. Seriously.

152
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:40,208
[ISHIMARU whimpers]

153
00:08:40,291 --> 00:08:42,250
That was actually
pretty good, huh?

154
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,541
Ohwada's speech patterns were
tricky to simulate,

155
00:08:44,625 --> 00:08:46,833
but I'm confident that's what
he would've wanted to say.

156
00:08:46,916 --> 00:08:50,291
I am touched truly and deeply...

157
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:52,041
Those words were like his-

158
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:53,833
I can feel his soul...

159
00:08:53,916 --> 00:08:56,250
It's moving through me!

160
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:59,750
[ISHIMARU yells]

161
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:02,166
Ishimaru, are you... okay?

162
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,041
No doubt, bro!

163
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,583
But who's Ishimaru?!

164
00:09:04,666 --> 00:09:10,375
I'm... Ishidaaa!

165
00:09:11,958 --> 00:09:15,583
[NAEGI] Well... at least it
got him over the hump, right?

166
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:18,208
[KIRIGIRI sighs]

167
00:09:21,208 --> 00:09:22,166
Sure thing!

168
00:09:22,250 --> 00:09:24,125
Oh... there's something else...

169
00:09:24,208 --> 00:09:26,666
Right after I began my
analysis of these files,

170
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:28,541
I found something
you'll want to see.

171
00:09:30,125 --> 00:09:32,375
[ALL gasp]

172
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:34,875
[NAEGI]
'Kay, what's up with that?

173
00:09:34,958 --> 00:09:38,125
[OHGAMI] It was my understanding
we were all complete strangers

174
00:09:38,208 --> 00:09:40,333
--before enrolling here.
--[ASAHINA] Wait, what if...

175
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:43,000
What if no one's really dead?

176
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:44,791
Of course they're dead.

177
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,125
We saw.

178
00:09:46,208 --> 00:09:47,916
One after another, we saw.

179
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,291
Either the bodies,
or their actual death.

180
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:52,875
[HAGAKURE] The pic's
gotta be fake.

181
00:09:52,958 --> 00:09:55,125
The damn bear's just
messing with us.

182
00:10:02,083 --> 00:10:06,541
[YAMADA screams]

183
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:07,541
Yamada?!

184
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:08,625
 Um...

185
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:10,750
[YAMADA] Sorry, sorry,
sorry, sorry!

186
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:12,083
Help me, Naegi!

187
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:14,250
Observe: I'm on my knees here!

188
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:15,083
Yeahhh...

189
00:10:15,166 --> 00:10:16,625
Can somebody explain?

190
00:10:16,708 --> 00:10:18,541
[KIRIGIRI] I just asked
a simple question.

191
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:21,875
Why he's using Alter Ego
after hours without permission.

192
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:23,250
Huh...?

193
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:25,125
I... I get lonely!

194
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:27,291
I just wanted
someone to talk to!

195
00:10:29,166 --> 00:10:30,666
[ALTER EGO] Neat-o!

196
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:33,583
You're so smart, Yamada!
Teach me more!

197
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:35,958
[YAMADA] It's not every day I
find someone who doesn't

198
00:10:36,041 --> 00:10:39,375
look at me sideways when I start
talking about what I'm into.

199
00:10:39,458 --> 00:10:41,250
Honestly, it was a first!

200
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:42,791
Normal people
aren't like that...

201
00:10:42,875 --> 00:10:45,041
N-Normal people
think I'm a freak...

202
00:10:46,291 --> 00:10:47,916
You do know he isn't real?

203
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,458
It's just a program.

204
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:51,708
Not that it's any
of my business...

205
00:10:51,791 --> 00:10:55,083
But I don't think this sort of
"friendship" is very healthy.

206
00:10:55,166 --> 00:10:57,916
Yes, we're all repulsed
by you, but still...

207
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,166
[YAMADA whines]

208
00:10:59,250 --> 00:11:00,208
[YAMADA] Don't rub it in!

209
00:11:00,291 --> 00:11:01,791
I know how pathetic I am...

210
00:11:01,875 --> 00:11:05,291
It's not like I've
got a lot of choices!

211
00:11:05,375 --> 00:11:06,500
Hoo-ah!

212
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:08,750
The sauna is amaze-balls!

213
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:10,125
[ASAHINA squeals]

214
00:11:10,208 --> 00:11:11,833
[NAEGI] Ishimaru...?

215
00:11:11,916 --> 00:11:15,125
[ISHIMARU (ISHIDA)] Why the hell
you callin' me that, dude?

216
00:11:15,208 --> 00:11:18,375
Keep that crap up, you're gonna
give me an identity crisis!

217
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,208
[ISHIMARU (ISHIDA)]
Anyway, screw that.

218
00:11:21,291 --> 00:11:24,208
I heard your li'l pow-wow and
did not dig what I heard!

219
00:11:24,291 --> 00:11:25,958
Alter Ego's mine, a-holes!

220
00:11:26,041 --> 00:11:27,125
[YAMADA] No!

221
00:11:27,208 --> 00:11:28,625
This is true love!

222
00:11:28,708 --> 00:11:31,041
I'll be damned if I
let you come betwixt us!

223
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:32,625
[KIRIGIRI] Enough. Both of you.

224
00:11:32,708 --> 00:11:34,708
We're not getting into a
tug-o'-war over this,

225
00:11:34,791 --> 00:11:35,500
understood?

226
00:11:35,583 --> 00:11:37,166
Call it Fujisaki's legacy,

227
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:39,750
but this computer may well be
our best chance to escape.

228
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:41,291
It belongs to everyone.

229
00:11:41,375 --> 00:11:44,166
So from now on no one's allowed
in here without permission.

230
00:12:01,250 --> 00:12:02,416
[ALTER EGO laughs]

231
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:04,875
[NAEGI] Fujisaki,
you're a certified genius.

232
00:12:04,958 --> 00:12:07,083
I can almost taste freedom!

233
00:12:07,166 --> 00:12:08,541
[doorbell rings]

234
00:12:10,291 --> 00:12:11,000
Yeah?

235
00:12:11,083 --> 00:12:12,625
[HAGAKURE] Naegi!

236
00:12:12,708 --> 00:12:13,708
[NAEGI] What is
wrong with you?!

237
00:12:13,791 --> 00:12:14,791
[NAEGI grunts]

238
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:15,833
Somebody dead?

239
00:12:15,916 --> 00:12:17,541
Whatcha say we
be suds buds?

240
00:12:17,625 --> 00:12:19,166
Keep each other squeaky?

241
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:20,500
You a "work your way up,"

242
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:22,166
or a "work your way
down" kind of guy?

243
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:23,500
I'm cool either way.

244
00:12:23,583 --> 00:12:25,541
Long's we don't forget
to wash behind the ears.

245
00:12:25,625 --> 00:12:27,666
[HAGAKURE laughs]

246
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,041
Ahhh, relax, we just
had to get clear

247
00:12:32,125 --> 00:12:34,625
of the surveillance cameras.

248
00:12:34,708 --> 00:12:36,750
[NAEGI] What's up?
Something bad?

249
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:38,208
[NAEGI gasps]

250
00:12:39,375 --> 00:12:41,500
[KIRIGIRI]
The laptop is missing.

251
00:12:41,583 --> 00:12:43,458
[YAMADA] And I'm
lookin' at you, Ishimaru!

252
00:12:43,541 --> 00:12:45,750
We all know you did it,
so be a man and 'fess up!

253
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:47,333
Really?

254
00:12:47,416 --> 00:12:49,250
I'll have you know I was a hall
monitor three-times-decorated

255
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:50,208
in my past life!

256
00:12:50,291 --> 00:12:51,375
That is enough.

257
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:53,666
Both of you can be
ruled out as suspects.

258
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:56,791
After yesterday, I programmed
Alter Ego to shriek

259
00:12:56,875 --> 00:12:58,666
if either one of
you came near it.

260
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:01,333
Clearly I overlooked
a less obvious threat.

261
00:13:01,416 --> 00:13:02,500
Clearly.

262
00:13:02,583 --> 00:13:04,291
The issue now becomes
how to narrow down

263
00:13:04,375 --> 00:13:05,583
the remaining suspects.

264
00:13:05,666 --> 00:13:08,083
None of us had any
reason to make off with it!

265
00:13:08,166 --> 00:13:08,875
Hmph.

266
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:10,083
Perhaps...

267
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:11,875
Or perhaps we're afraid
to admit the truth.

268
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:13,416
Consider this:

269
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,291
We've a traitor in our ranks.

270
00:13:15,375 --> 00:13:16,708
[ALL gasp]

271
00:13:16,791 --> 00:13:18,666
[TOGAMI] The notion leapt
from possible to probable

272
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:20,666
in my mind some time ago.

273
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:22,708
Wouldn't a mole be
par for the course?

274
00:13:22,791 --> 00:13:25,416
An excellent way to ensure
the game went smoothly.

275
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,791
See to it the pieces
moved as desired.

276
00:13:27,875 --> 00:13:29,541
Correct?

277
00:13:29,625 --> 00:13:32,333
Oh, come on! If I'm the only
one who thought of this,

278
00:13:32,416 --> 00:13:33,916
the rest of you aren't
even trying.

279
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,791
[school bells chime]

280
00:13:35,875 --> 00:13:38,333
[MONOKUMA] Oh dear,
look at the time!

281
00:13:38,416 --> 00:13:41,291
Ten o'clock and all's hell!

282
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:43,000
Curfew, ladies and germs!

283
00:13:43,083 --> 00:13:44,458
Nighty-night!

284
00:13:52,416 --> 00:13:53,625
[NAEGI] Seriously?

285
00:13:53,708 --> 00:13:55,125
Wow. Small group today.

286
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:58,125
[ASAHINA] Yeah... Like, where
are Hagakure and Celestia?

287
00:13:58,208 --> 00:13:59,375
The whole time we've lived here,

288
00:13:59,458 --> 00:14:00,916
they haven't missed
breakfast once!

289
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,375
And the freaks! They
should be here, too!

290
00:14:03,458 --> 00:14:06,375
I have a terrible
feeling something's wrong.

291
00:14:06,458 --> 00:14:08,750
We should probably
look for them.

292
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:12,333
Ohgami, I'd like you
to search the dormitory.

293
00:14:12,416 --> 00:14:15,083
Naegi, I'll leave the
first floor to you.

294
00:14:15,166 --> 00:14:17,666
I'll comb the second floor.

295
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:19,333
Cool. And I'll take the third!

296
00:14:19,416 --> 00:14:20,958
[door creaks]

297
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:27,666
[ASAHINA gasps]

298
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:30,583
Somebody help!

299
00:14:34,583 --> 00:14:36,083
I was careless.

300
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:38,083
What cretin
did this to you?

301
00:14:38,166 --> 00:14:39,750
[CELESTIA] It was rather odd...

302
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:42,833
Whoever it was went to great
lengths to hide their face.

303
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:44,416
And struck me with that.

304
00:14:45,625 --> 00:14:47,875
[NAEGI] Justice Hammer #1?

305
00:14:47,958 --> 00:14:48,666
[CELESTIA gasps]

306
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:50,291
Yamada's in grave danger!

307
00:14:50,375 --> 00:14:52,666
The person who did this
to me kidnapped him!

308
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:53,583
[gasping]

309
00:14:53,666 --> 00:14:54,625
They hung a left.

310
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:56,833
I saw them as I
was blacking out!

311
00:14:56,916 --> 00:14:58,375
Hung a left, huh?

312
00:14:58,458 --> 00:15:00,583
That puts them on the stairwell
leading to the second floor.

313
00:15:00,666 --> 00:15:01,250
Oh no!

314
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:02,708
Kiri's down there!

315
00:15:05,250 --> 00:15:06,458
Togami!

316
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:09,166
Please tell me you've
seen Kiri or Yamada!

317
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:11,000
Since when's it
our job to watch 'em?!

318
00:15:11,083 --> 00:15:12,333
Is something the matter?

319
00:15:12,416 --> 00:15:13,500
Might be...

320
00:15:13,583 --> 00:15:14,958
[OHGAMI] Over here!

321
00:15:16,041 --> 00:15:17,916
[YAMADA grunts]

322
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,666
What happened to you?!

323
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:20,875
[NAEGI gasps]

324
00:15:20,958 --> 00:15:23,541
[NAEGI] Another one of
those weird hammers?

325
00:15:23,625 --> 00:15:25,208
Are you all right?

326
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:28,541
I can't believe it...
Justice Robo attacked me!

327
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:30,333
Hardly the
time to be cute.

328
00:15:30,416 --> 00:15:32,500
[CELESTIA] He's not
being cute, trust me.

329
00:15:32,583 --> 00:15:34,166
Izzat a camera?!

330
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:36,708
[CELESTIA] Yes. I found it
in the game room.

331
00:15:36,791 --> 00:15:37,750
Look.

332
00:15:37,833 --> 00:15:40,041
[ASAHINA] Look at what?

333
00:15:40,125 --> 00:15:42,166
[TOGAMI] Well. Okay.

334
00:15:42,250 --> 00:15:44,666
[CELESTIA] Bizarre,
I know, but there it is.

335
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:46,833
[ASAHINA] We gotta go
after this maniac!

336
00:15:46,916 --> 00:15:49,750
[YAMADA] You guys mind if I
take five in the nurse's office

337
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:51,250
while you do?

338
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:53,291
[CELESTIA] Fine... The rest
of us will split into teams.

339
00:16:03,541 --> 00:16:06,333
[FUKAWA (SHO) giggles]

340
00:16:10,083 --> 00:16:13,458
[CELESTIA shrieks]

341
00:16:13,541 --> 00:16:14,583
[ASAHINA] What happened?!

342
00:16:14,666 --> 00:16:16,833
[CELESTIA groans]

343
00:16:16,916 --> 00:16:17,541
[NAEGI] Celestia!

344
00:16:17,625 --> 00:16:19,000
Are you--?!

345
00:16:19,083 --> 00:16:21,083
It's all right,
I wasn't injured.

346
00:16:21,166 --> 00:16:23,916
I saw Justice Robo make
a dash for the physics lab.

347
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,625
He's cornered himself, then.

348
00:16:25,708 --> 00:16:27,125
[FUKAWA (SHO) sneezes]

349
00:16:27,208 --> 00:16:29,125
Oh... Hello?

350
00:16:29,208 --> 00:16:30,541
You've gotta
be kidding me.

351
00:16:30,625 --> 00:16:32,916
Will you pick a
personality already?!

352
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:33,750
[YAMADA screams]

353
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:34,958
That's not good.

354
00:16:35,041 --> 00:16:37,125
Damn it all! One
thing at a time!

355
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:39,250
Oh, wait! Don't leave me!

356
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:41,583
You three check
on Yamada!

357
00:16:41,666 --> 00:16:44,500
Yes, I think that's the
best course of action.

358
00:16:55,666 --> 00:16:57,375
[NAEGI screams]

359
00:16:57,458 --> 00:16:59,500
Did... Did he pass out?

360
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:00,500
I'm sorry...

361
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:02,666
Odds are he's dead.

362
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:04,875
[CELESTIA] Another one?

363
00:17:04,958 --> 00:17:07,250
But I saw our man on
the third floor...

364
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:09,875
How is this possible?

365
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:14,458
[MONOKUMA]
♪ Bum-bum-bum-buuuum! ♪

366
00:17:14,541 --> 00:17:16,583
Corpse alert, junior detectives!

367
00:17:16,666 --> 00:17:22,166
You know the drill:
investi-ma-gation, then, trial!

368
00:17:25,208 --> 00:17:26,625
I... I'm sorry...

369
00:17:26,708 --> 00:17:27,875
I feel like...

370
00:17:27,958 --> 00:17:29,458
like I'm gonna puke...

371
00:17:29,541 --> 00:17:31,041
Deep breaths, dear.

372
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:34,000
Here. Let's get you to the
lady's room, shall we?

373
00:17:34,083 --> 00:17:35,208
Naegi. Please...

374
00:17:35,291 --> 00:17:37,416
Find the others and
tell them Yamada's dead.

375
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:49,458
Hey, guys!

376
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:51,666
Where are you?!

377
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:55,916
[NAEGI gasps]

378
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:01,166
[NAEGI] Ishimaru!

379
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:02,583
Fukawa!

380
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:04,791
She's alive; merely passed out
from the sight of blood.

381
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:07,458
And I'm afraid the murderer had
already made good his escape

382
00:18:07,541 --> 00:18:08,625
by the time we got here.

383
00:18:08,708 --> 00:18:11,208
Another of these
silly hammers was used.

384
00:18:11,291 --> 00:18:12,541
But "four?"

385
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:14,958
We've seen One and Two,
why is this not Three?

386
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:18,291
Yeah, 'bout that...

387
00:18:18,375 --> 00:18:21,041
Somebody used Number Three
to kill Yamada.

388
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:21,583
[TOGAMI gasps[

389
00:18:21,666 --> 00:18:22,958
You're joking!

390
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:25,958
[NAEGI] Celestia?!

391
00:18:26,041 --> 00:18:26,791
It...

392
00:18:26,875 --> 00:18:28,250
It's so, ghoulish...

393
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:29,708
Huh...?

394
00:18:32,083 --> 00:18:33,333
[NAEGI] What's going on?!

395
00:18:33,416 --> 00:18:34,916
Where'd the body go?!

396
00:18:35,875 --> 00:18:37,083
[OHGAMI] Asahina!

397
00:18:37,166 --> 00:18:38,625
We-We were...

398
00:18:38,708 --> 00:18:42,041
We were in the bathroom for
maybe a couple minutes at most.

399
00:18:42,125 --> 00:18:42,916
And then...

400
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,541
when we came back...

401
00:18:44,625 --> 00:18:46,791
This has to be the
killer's handiwork.

402
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:49,333
If they're trying to
confuse us, it's working.

403
00:18:49,416 --> 00:18:51,166
We're going to die...

404
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:53,500
Picked off one by one
'til there's...

405
00:18:53,583 --> 00:18:55,458
'til there's no one...

406
00:18:55,541 --> 00:18:57,750
Exactly like they were.

407
00:18:57,833 --> 00:19:00,666
Why would the killer have
made off with Yamada's corpse?

408
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:03,750
Two murders within moments
of each other, then...

409
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:06,333
evidence already
discovered is moved.

410
00:19:06,416 --> 00:19:07,375
Waitaminnit, what?

411
00:19:07,458 --> 00:19:08,916
Two murders?!

412
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,541
What are you talking about?

413
00:19:10,625 --> 00:19:13,583
Ishimaru's no longer
among the living...

414
00:19:13,666 --> 00:19:15,875
We found him in the
physics lab storage room.

415
00:19:15,958 --> 00:19:16,916
[ASAHINA] Noooo!

416
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,500
Celestia's right!

417
00:19:18,583 --> 00:19:19,875
We are all gonna die!

418
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:21,208
Darling, get
a hold of yourself.

419
00:19:21,291 --> 00:19:22,250
Don't say that.

420
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:23,583
Whoa, what is wrong with us?!

421
00:19:23,666 --> 00:19:25,791
We left Fukawa back at the lab!

422
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:27,250
Naegi, wait!

423
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:31,958
[FUKAWA whimpers]

424
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:33,250
That's a relief.

425
00:19:33,333 --> 00:19:34,833
[OHGAMI] Naegi.

426
00:19:34,916 --> 00:19:38,333
If I see what I think I do,
this is beyond the pale.

427
00:19:38,416 --> 00:19:39,791
[NAEGI gasps]

428
00:19:39,875 --> 00:19:43,166
[NAEGI] Now Ishimaru's
corpse is gone!

429
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:44,666
Oh dear...

430
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,500
What in heaven's name could
the murderer be playing at?

431
00:19:46,583 --> 00:19:48,958
He, or she, is
trying to confound us.

432
00:19:49,041 --> 00:19:51,666
The bodies are obviously
hidden somewhere.

433
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:53,083
Hang on...

434
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:55,541
Celestia has a point;
why bother hiding 'em at all?

435
00:19:55,625 --> 00:19:57,333
[CELESTIA] Well, it couldn't
have been any of us,

436
00:19:57,416 --> 00:19:59,625
so we'll just have to
ask him when we find him.

437
00:19:59,708 --> 00:20:01,625
[ASAHINA] There's a bloodthirsty
maniac on the loose!

438
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:04,416
[TOGAMI] Stop and think
for a moment.

439
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,083
First: The timing.

440
00:20:06,166 --> 00:20:09,541
This all unfolded in a precisely
balanced sequence impossible

441
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:11,291
for a sole perpetrator
to have carried out.

442
00:20:11,375 --> 00:20:13,250
Uhh... That makes sense.

443
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:15,041
Second, and most importantly:

444
00:20:15,125 --> 00:20:16,500
There are two classmates of ours

445
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:18,541
rather tellingly
unaccounted for.

446
00:20:18,625 --> 00:20:19,375
Hold up...

447
00:20:19,458 --> 00:20:20,625
I know what you're thinking.

448
00:20:20,708 --> 00:20:22,916
But Kirigiri was with
us all in the cafeteria.

449
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,958
That was when we
heard Celestia scream.

450
00:20:25,041 --> 00:20:26,333
Interesting...

451
00:20:26,416 --> 00:20:29,333
Well that would appear
to give her a decent alibi.

452
00:20:29,416 --> 00:20:30,875
Yes. Naturally.

453
00:20:30,958 --> 00:20:33,333
But I suppose that points
the finger at Hagakure

454
00:20:33,416 --> 00:20:35,625
being Justice Robo,
doesn't it?

455
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:38,041
Which means the rest of
us aren't in danger.

456
00:20:38,125 --> 00:20:41,125
The school rules were abundantly
clear on that point.

457
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:42,000
[NAEGI] Right...

458
00:20:42,083 --> 00:20:44,958
Only two victims per murderer.

459
00:20:45,041 --> 00:20:46,208
Hah!

460
00:20:46,291 --> 00:20:50,500
And anyone who breaks
the rules gets puréed!

461
00:20:50,583 --> 00:20:51,208
[NAEGI gasps]

462
00:20:51,291 --> 00:20:52,375
Please not this again!

463
00:20:52,458 --> 00:20:53,916
Just for confirmation...

464
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,833
Can we assume this
wasn't your handiwork?

465
00:20:55,916 --> 00:20:56,875
Oh, puh-lease!

466
00:20:56,958 --> 00:20:58,375
I wouldn'ta done
something like this!

467
00:20:58,458 --> 00:21:01,375
My taste in prey is way too
particular, sugar lips!

468
00:21:01,458 --> 00:21:02,916
--They gotta be hawt!
--All right then,

469
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,375
let's find the bodies.

470
00:21:07,458 --> 00:21:09,583
[NAEGI] Obviously we
gotta find them.

471
00:21:09,666 --> 00:21:11,583
But where do we even look?

472
00:21:11,666 --> 00:21:13,041
Search the room.

473
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:17,541
Hmm...

474
00:21:17,625 --> 00:21:18,916
[ASAHINA grunts]

475
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,166
Dang it. Guess it's locked.

476
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:22,625
Every detail.

477
00:21:24,125 --> 00:21:25,500
[FUKAWA (SHO) yells]

478
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:31,916
[CELESTIA] Naegi...

479
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,375
Togami...

480
00:21:38,583 --> 00:21:39,958
[NAEGI gasps]

481
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:48,541
It's so awful!

482
00:21:48,625 --> 00:21:51,083
Who would do this?

483
00:21:51,166 --> 00:21:53,208
They were...

484
00:21:53,291 --> 00:21:55,125
They were innocent!

485
00:21:55,208 --> 00:21:59,416
[ASAHINA sobs]

486
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:01,791
[YAMADA grunts softly]

487
00:22:01,875 --> 00:22:02,750
He's alive!

488
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:03,791
[NAEGI gasps]

489
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:06,833
Hang in there!
We'll get some help!

490
00:22:06,916 --> 00:22:09,958
Who... are you...?

491
00:22:10,041 --> 00:22:11,125
Oh, yeah...

492
00:22:11,208 --> 00:22:12,291
Right...

493
00:22:12,375 --> 00:22:13,875
We all...

494
00:22:13,958 --> 00:22:16,333
...go way back, don't we...?

495
00:22:16,416 --> 00:22:19,000
Been friends forever...

496
00:22:19,083 --> 00:22:22,166
His poor brain's been
scrambled by the head trauma.

497
00:22:22,250 --> 00:22:23,333
The light...

498
00:22:23,416 --> 00:22:25,416
It's beautiful...

499
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:28,166
The light's
spreading everywhere...

500
00:22:28,250 --> 00:22:29,416
Who did this to you?

501
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:30,833
Tell us, please!

502
00:22:30,916 --> 00:22:32,708
We'll bring them to justice.

503
00:22:32,791 --> 00:22:34,750
Help us do that, buddy.

504
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:37,958
So... cold...

505
00:22:38,041 --> 00:22:40,333
I'll try to remember...

506
00:22:40,416 --> 00:22:41,083
It...

507
00:22:41,166 --> 00:22:42,041
was...

508
00:22:42,125 --> 00:22:43,416
Yasu...

509
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:45,666
hii--ro...

510
00:22:47,250 --> 00:22:48,791
[ASAHINA gasps]

511
00:22:48,875 --> 00:22:50,333
[ASAHINA whimpers]

512
00:22:50,416 --> 00:22:53,166
[MONOKUMA]
♪ Ba-ba-ba-buuuum! ♪

513
00:22:53,250 --> 00:22:55,583
Double corpse alert, chickadees!

514
00:22:55,666 --> 00:22:59,666
Stop me if you've heard this
one: investigation, then, trial!

